        "section_label": "The Metabo Story",
        "title": "German Engineering Since 1924",
        "paragraph_1": "In 1924, Albrecht Schnizler and Julius Closs founded Schnizler GmbH in a former brewery in Nurtingen, Germany. Schnizler had already developed his first hand drill — the Metallbohrdreher (metal drill turner) — in 1923, which sold over 50,000 units worldwide. The brand name Metabo was derived from that original product in 1928, and the company has been engineering professional power tools at the same Nurtingen site for over 100 years.",
        "paragraph_2": "Today, Metabo is recognised globally as the angle grinder specialist and a leader in cordless technology. Their LiHD (Lithium-ion High Density) battery platform delivers up to 67% more power than standard Li-ion packs, covering the full power range up to 3,200 watts — a first for any cordless manufacturer. Combined with the Cordless Alliance System (CAS), which connects over 45 brands and 450+ tools on a single 18V battery platform, Metabo gives trade professionals unmatched flexibility and performance on site.",
