    "faq": {
      "type": "brand-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is Metabo LiHD battery technology?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>LiHD (Lithium-ion High Density)</strong> is Metabo's proprietary battery technology. The cells contain more active material, more tightly packed than standard Li-ion, delivering up to 67% more power in a similar-sized pack. Metabo is the only manufacturer to cover the full cordless power range up to 3,200 watts thanks to LiHD. Packs are available from 4.0Ah up to 10.0Ah.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the Cordless Alliance System (CAS)?",
            "answer": "<p>The <strong>Cordless Alliance System (CAS)</strong> is the world's first cross-manufacturer 18V battery platform. Over 45 professional tool brands — including Metabo, Mafell, Rothenberger and Collomix — share 100% compatible batteries, chargers and tools. That means one Metabo LiHD battery powers over 450 tools from dozens of brands, maximising your investment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What warranty do Metabo tools come with?",
            "answer": "<p>Metabo power tools come with a <strong>3-year manufacturer warranty</strong> when registered within 4 weeks of purchase at metabo-service.com. Metabo also provides a 3-year warranty on all battery packs and chargers with no limitation on charging cycles and no registration required. As an official Metabo stockist, Invicta Tools can assist with all warranty claims.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Why is Metabo considered the angle grinder specialist?",
            "answer": "<p>Metabo has led angle grinder innovation for decades. They are the <strong>only manufacturer with a true mechanical safety clutch (S-automatic)</strong> built into every grinder — patented since 1966, it decouples the motor instantly if the disc jams to prevent kickback. Their range spans 115mm to 230mm, includes flat-head models for confined spaces, specialist Inox models for stainless steel, and a disc brake that stops the wheel in under 2 seconds.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you offer trade pricing on Metabo?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. We offer <strong>competitive trade pricing</strong> across the full Metabo range including angle grinders, cordless tools, LiHD batteries and accessories. Contact our trade team on <strong>01843 593 440</strong> or email <strong>sales@invictatools.co.uk</strong> for volume discounts and trade account enquiries. Free next-day delivery on all orders over £99.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are older Metabo 18V batteries compatible with new LiHD tools?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. All Metabo 18V batteries produced since 2009 are fully compatible with current Metabo 18V tools. However, for maximum performance from LiHD-rated tools, we recommend using <strong>LiHD battery packs</strong> (4.0Ah, 5.5Ah, 8.0Ah or 10.0Ah) as they deliver significantly more power and runtime than standard Li-ion packs. All batteries are also CAS-compatible with 45+ partner brands.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
